244
00:16:21,323 --> 00:16:24,386
And we are usually constructing our videos like that

245
00:16:24,386 --> 00:16:27,428
because long story short, it works.

246
00:16:27,428 --> 00:16:31,591
And the third part is the overarching narrative.

247
00:16:32,092 --> 00:16:37,256
So we have defined a universe with our communication, a universe of this world of mine,

248
00:16:37,256 --> 00:16:44,983
and we wanted every bit of content, no matter if it was video or key visual or an interview

249
00:16:44,983 --> 00:16:48,687
or whatever it was, it had to fit that tonality of the game.

250
00:16:49,347 --> 00:16:55,975
it had to fit all of those elements of the identity of the game, if that makes sense,

251
00:16:55,975 --> 00:17:03,944
because that helped and that defined what this War of Mine really was.

252
00:17:05,039 --> 00:17:10,281
really is. And usually when we think about game marketing, when we think about campaign, we think

253
00:17:10,281 --> 00:17:16,382
short term, we focus on the launch window and that makes sense because this is the most important

254
00:17:16,382 --> 00:17:25,365
period in your campaign because how well your game is doing in the launch video highly influences

255
00:17:25,365 --> 00:17:26,365
the overall

256
00:17:27,009 --> 00:17:31,612
result of your campaign and the overall success of your game, if you will.

257
00:17:31,612 --> 00:17:40,438
But at the same time, supporting your game long-term and preparing and running this long-term campaign

258
00:17:40,438 --> 00:17:43,860
can help a lot and can get you a long way.

259
00:17:43,860 --> 00:17:49,985
So because of that, maintaining the relationship with our community in social media

260
00:17:49,985 --> 00:17:53,847
is also a very important part of what we do.

261
00:17:54,811 --> 00:18:00,054
we use social media and we perceive social media as a communication channel.

262
00:18:00,054 --> 00:18:06,257
So we use paid media quite a bit, I would say, those paid posts and so on and so on.

263
00:18:06,257 --> 00:18:13,560
But at the same time, social media as a channel is also a part of the universe of our game.

264
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:19,203
So we treat it in that manner as well. So we post all of those content bits that

265
00:18:19,203 --> 00:18:22,565
could be interesting for those people who are very much into our game.

266
00:18:23,245 --> 00:18:29,808
So, because of that, we treat social media as a part of the, let's call it, enhanced edition of the game.

267
00:18:29,808 --> 00:18:36,150
So, if you like the experience, you can find additional bits and pieces of that experience in social media.

268
00:18:36,150 --> 00:18:39,932
It's kind of a limited DVD, you know what I'm talking about.

269
00:18:39,932 --> 00:18:42,833
So, yeah, and it works because...

270
00:18:43,471 --> 00:18:48,696
Our community is very engaged and very active.

271
00:18:48,696 --> 00:18:52,759
And we do not limit the activity of our community.

272
00:18:52,759 --> 00:18:55,662
We value that part very much.

273
00:18:55,662 --> 00:18:59,405
And right now we've got a board game happening

274
00:18:59,405 --> 00:19:01,387
and we love the board game.

275
00:19:01,387 --> 00:19:02,668
It's not our initiative,

276
00:19:02,668 --> 00:19:04,669
but we support that initiative a lot.

277
00:19:05,491 --> 00:19:10,157
We almost had an independent movie based on our game,

278
00:19:10,157 --> 00:19:13,041
and for us it's okay, because we never perceived

279
00:19:13,041 --> 00:19:15,605
This War of Mine as a beginning of the franchise.

280
00:19:15,605 --> 00:19:18,008
We do not plan to make a sequel,

281
00:19:18,008 --> 00:19:20,712
but at the same time, we like the fact...

282
00:19:20,932 --> 00:19:26,757
that our community is active and co-creates the universe of this world of mine with us.

283
00:19:26,757 --> 00:19:34,524
And we are happy about it. We do not limit the activities as I said before, but we do maintain

284
00:19:34,524 --> 00:19:39,568
the coherency of the brand. So we have to make sure that every bit of the

285
00:19:39,588 --> 00:19:41,848
content that is related to the game.

286
00:19:41,848 --> 00:19:44,749
No matter if we are creating the content

287
00:19:44,749 --> 00:19:47,850
or our gamers are, it should be in line

288
00:19:47,850 --> 00:19:50,311
with the identity of the game, so everyone

289
00:19:50,311 --> 00:19:54,272
would know that this World of Mine is what it is.

290
00:19:54,272 --> 00:19:56,733
And it works for us, as I said, because people

291
00:19:56,733 --> 00:19:58,613
seem to like the game, even though.

292
00:19:59,898 --> 00:20:07,803
Yeah, even though it can be a struggle, it can be exhausting and sometimes it's even exhausting for me.

293
00:20:07,803 --> 00:20:14,268
And we had and actually we have good media coverage, not only gaming wise, not only in gaming media,

294
00:20:14,268 --> 00:20:19,832
but in let's call it mainstream media as well. And I strongly believe that we achieved that because

295
00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:27,774
We are focusing on emotions, we are focusing on that mind premise and tech, gameplay, all of those

296
00:20:27,774 --> 00:20:35,656
features as important as those are, those only follow and those support our communication,

297
00:20:35,656 --> 00:20:38,356
but our communication is focused on the big idea, right?

298
00:20:39,337 --> 00:20:43,899
And we won some awards and we had good sales.

299
00:20:43,899 --> 00:20:46,920
And when it comes to sales,

300
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:49,621
I strongly believe that the first part,

301
00:20:49,621 --> 00:20:52,563
meaning the sales within the launch windows,

302
00:20:52,563 --> 00:20:55,284
those are mostly based...

303
00:20:56,365 --> 00:21:01,950
on the fact if your campaign, if your marketing campaign is good or not.

304
00:21:01,950 --> 00:21:09,737
But at the same time, long-term sales rely mostly on the quality of the game itself.

305
00:21:11,198 --> 00:21:17,179
You can have an exceptional campaign, but if you have a mediocre game, you won't have good sales,

306
00:21:17,179 --> 00:21:24,921
which is kind of an obvious thing, but my point is that your marketing campaign is an integral part of your game,

307
00:21:24,921 --> 00:21:28,422
not something that is next to it or whatever.

308
00:21:28,422 --> 00:21:32,303
You have to make it a coherent thing, and those elements...

309
00:21:33,004 --> 00:21:36,266
should support each other very strongly.

310
00:21:36,266 --> 00:21:39,569
And yeah, we learned a lot in the process,

311
00:21:39,569 --> 00:21:42,652
not only designing, but running the campaign.

312
00:21:42,652 --> 00:21:44,733
Early into the campaign,

313
00:21:44,733 --> 00:21:47,195
just after we have released the trailer,

314
00:21:47,195 --> 00:21:47,896
I played.

315
00:21:48,776 --> 00:21:53,558
A while ago, Emir, a survivor from Sarajevo, reached us

316
00:21:53,558 --> 00:21:56,099
and we were very happy about it because he told us

317
00:21:56,099 --> 00:21:57,179
that he liked the game very much.

318
00:21:57,179 --> 00:21:59,140
And we're like, okay, so it works.

319
00:21:59,140 --> 00:22:01,641
So we are up to something.

320
00:22:01,641 --> 00:22:03,242
This is it, we've got it.

321
00:22:03,242 --> 00:22:05,703
So we invited him to share the stories.

322
00:22:05,703 --> 00:22:08,223
He came to Poland, he came to Warsaw,

323
00:22:08,223 --> 00:22:10,985
and together we have created a launch trailer for the game.

324
00:22:11,665 --> 00:22:17,028
And that launch trailer combined his memoirs with our gameplay,

325
00:22:17,028 --> 00:22:20,611
so we cooperated and we achieved a great result.

326
00:22:20,611 --> 00:22:22,012
We love the trailer very much.

327
00:22:22,012 --> 00:22:24,833
It's kind of a live action mix with gameplay.

328
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:27,095
You can Google it up because I don't have,

329
00:22:27,095 --> 00:22:29,496
unfortunately, time right now to play all the bits.

330
00:22:30,237 --> 00:22:32,338
but we were quite happy about it.

331
00:22:32,338 --> 00:22:34,799
And the lesson here is that sometimes

332
00:22:34,799 --> 00:22:37,200
those opportunities emerge.

333
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:39,141
And you have to push things forward

334
00:22:39,141 --> 00:22:41,862
just to chase those opportunities and use them

335
00:22:41,862 --> 00:22:46,544
because they can get you really, really far.

336
00:22:46,544 --> 00:22:49,585
But at the same time, when it comes to the cooperation,

337
00:22:49,585 --> 00:22:53,067
you will cooperate with some external partners,

338
00:22:53,067 --> 00:22:56,788
some agencies, some video production houses and such.

339
00:22:57,088 --> 00:23:00,311
And those cooperations can be good or bad,

340
00:23:00,311 --> 00:23:03,513
or they can fall somewhere in between,

341
00:23:03,513 --> 00:23:06,696
but you have to maintain,

342
00:23:06,696 --> 00:23:09,898
no matter how much you trust your partner,

343
00:23:09,898 --> 00:23:13,041
you should always, always maintain the art direction.

344
00:23:13,041 --> 00:23:14,542
You should keep it under your control.

345
00:23:14,542 --> 00:23:17,964
Because at the end of the day, it is your game.

346
00:23:18,705 --> 00:23:22,507
And at the end of the day, it is your communication,

347
00:23:22,507 --> 00:23:26,369
your campaign, and your results that you want to achieve.

348
00:23:26,369 --> 00:23:28,971
And no one from outside of the company actually

349
00:23:28,971 --> 00:23:33,294
can feel the matter of your game as well as you do.

350
00:23:33,294 --> 00:23:36,275
So you should be the one making those decisions.

351
00:23:36,275 --> 00:23:38,957
Because even if you have a poor partner,

352
00:23:38,957 --> 00:23:44,020
if you have a good control over the art direction,

353
00:23:45,101 --> 00:23:47,122
you will be just fine.

354
00:23:47,122 --> 00:23:51,445
And yeah, and the piracy, which is a fun topic, isn't it?

355
00:23:51,445 --> 00:23:55,648
So we encountered that problem at one point,

356
00:23:55,648 --> 00:23:58,991
but we decided not to fight with the piracy

357
00:23:58,991 --> 00:24:01,373
because we are not Metallica.

358
00:24:01,373 --> 00:24:06,837
But instead of that, we decided to show some empathy.

359
00:24:07,497 --> 00:24:14,543
So Karol, a colleague of mine from our team, he posted a message on Pirate Bay thanking,

360
00:24:14,543 --> 00:24:21,649
actually thanking people for liking the game and for showing interest in our game.

361
00:24:21,649 --> 00:24:27,393
He encouraged them to buy the game, but at the same time he told them, okay guys, I know that

362
00:24:27,393 --> 00:24:33,198
for many reasons maybe you cannot buy the game, so I'm gonna share some Steam codes with you.

363
00:24:33,198 --> 00:24:36,480
And PR-wise it was a very good move because

364
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:43,530
it didn't cost much, you know, it was, those were just few codes, but at the same time we have gained

365
00:24:43,530 --> 00:24:51,461
good media coverage, we have gained good feedback from our gamers, from our players, but honestly...

366
00:24:52,062 --> 00:24:55,364
while it was a PR move, at the same time it wasn't.

367
00:24:55,364 --> 00:24:58,266
Because this is what we believe.

368
00:24:58,266 --> 00:25:01,449
All the people that play your game

369
00:25:01,449 --> 00:25:02,729
are part of your community.

370
00:25:02,729 --> 00:25:05,371
And OK, maybe they didn't pay for your game,

371
00:25:05,371 --> 00:25:08,834
but they can contribute in so many different ways.

372
00:25:08,834 --> 00:25:09,654
They can.

373
00:25:10,568 --> 00:25:16,850
give you good feedback. They can enhance your reach, the reach of your communication. They can

374
00:25:16,850 --> 00:25:23,152
build awareness for your game. So maybe they won't give you their money, but their friends may,

375
00:25:23,152 --> 00:25:28,934
or friends of their friends, and so on and so on and so on. So fighting with people, you will gain

376
00:25:28,934 --> 00:25:34,936
nothing. You will lose energy, you will lose time, and you will lose money. But supporting each other

377
00:25:34,936 --> 00:25:38,036
and maintaining good relations with your community, you can...

378
00:25:38,794 --> 00:25:42,116
win something at the end of the day and probably you will.

379
00:25:42,116 --> 00:25:45,518
And yeah, and last but not least,

380
00:25:45,518 --> 00:25:49,781
because our game is about casualties of war

381
00:25:49,781 --> 00:25:53,804
and the expansion pack titled The Little Ones

382
00:25:53,804 --> 00:25:57,586
is about kids, it's about children during the time of war,

383
00:25:57,586 --> 00:26:01,669
we decided to start the cooperation with War Child.

384
00:26:01,669 --> 00:26:03,610
And that was amazing for us because

385
00:26:04,490 --> 00:26:10,873
We not only helped a lot because we have gathered a significant amount of money for them,

386
00:26:10,873 --> 00:26:15,294
but it allowed us to reach mainstream media once more.

387
00:26:15,294 --> 00:26:19,316
But our learning was that no matter how good the initiative is,

388
00:26:19,316 --> 00:26:26,258
no matter how good your idea for an activity, for an activation or a short campaign burst is,

389
00:26:26,999 --> 00:26:34,021
Usually it's a one-shot and it was like that even in terms of our cooperation with War Child,

390
00:26:34,021 --> 00:26:40,763
because it's a long-term cooperation, we are cooperating still, but even after we gathered

391
00:26:40,763 --> 00:26:47,606
a significant amount of money, it was hard for us to gain interest of media once again.

392
00:26:47,606 --> 00:26:51,227
So they covered the story once, but then it wasn't.

393
00:26:51,807 --> 00:26:59,512
hip enough maybe. So I think that while maintaining coherency and consistency is crucial when it comes

394
00:26:59,512 --> 00:27:05,435
to the efficient campaign, at the same time you should diversify your activities

395
00:27:05,435 --> 00:27:08,117
and keep them fresh to maintain the hype simply.

396
00:27:09,620 --> 00:27:11,541
Okay, so just to wrap things up,

397
00:27:11,541 --> 00:27:13,463
as I have like three minutes more,

398
00:27:13,463 --> 00:27:17,606
these are the key takeouts, at least from my perspective,

399
00:27:17,606 --> 00:27:20,809
when it comes to this World of Mine and its campaign.

400
00:27:20,809 --> 00:27:24,271
So first and foremost, we worked on our strategy

401
00:27:24,271 --> 00:27:25,852
quite a lot, I would say.

402
00:27:25,852 --> 00:27:27,534
We iterated and iterated.

403
00:27:27,534 --> 00:27:29,295
We wanted to polish it.

404
00:27:29,715 --> 00:27:31,336
as well as we could.

405
00:27:31,336 --> 00:27:34,998
So working on your strategy as long as necessary is crucial,

406
00:27:34,998 --> 00:27:37,979
but once you have it, you should stick to it

407
00:27:37,979 --> 00:27:40,380
and use it as a foundation,

408
00:27:40,380 --> 00:27:42,861
not only for the first part of the campaign

409
00:27:42,861 --> 00:27:45,202
or the first trailer, launch trailer,

410
00:27:45,202 --> 00:27:46,562
however you want to call it,

411
00:27:46,562 --> 00:27:50,524
but for the whole thing, for the long-term activity.

412
00:27:50,524 --> 00:27:55,346
Everything you do, everything you treat as a follow-up.

413
00:27:55,746 --> 00:27:59,767
for the first hit should be in line with that strategy.

414
00:27:59,767 --> 00:28:02,649
And start your marketing work early

415
00:28:02,649 --> 00:28:05,069
in the development process, I would say,

416
00:28:05,069 --> 00:28:07,510
because you should, at least we do,

417
00:28:07,510 --> 00:28:09,311
but I think that you should as well

418
00:28:09,311 --> 00:28:12,692
treat your marketing campaign as a part of your game.

419
00:28:12,692 --> 00:28:14,553
It is the same universe.

420
00:28:14,553 --> 00:28:17,374
It should be made from the ground up

421
00:28:17,374 --> 00:28:21,495
in close cooperation with your dev team.

422
00:28:22,095 --> 00:28:24,437
Make your media planning adequate.

423
00:28:24,437 --> 00:28:27,059
I mean, of course, it is about reach,

424
00:28:27,059 --> 00:28:28,560
it is about awareness,

425
00:28:28,560 --> 00:28:31,862
and it is about feedback from your community,

426
00:28:31,862 --> 00:28:32,842
if that makes sense.

427
00:28:32,842 --> 00:28:35,764
But at the same time, the reach and awareness

428
00:28:35,764 --> 00:28:39,047
and all of those factors are important

429
00:28:39,047 --> 00:28:42,809
as long as you use them in the right channels.

430
00:28:43,169 --> 00:28:44,750
Otherwise, it's just buzz.

431
00:28:44,750 --> 00:28:50,433
You do not want to spend all the money to be on TV and on in the radio or whatever.

432
00:28:50,433 --> 00:28:52,734
You want to be where you want to be.

433
00:28:52,734 --> 00:28:57,217
Those specific channels in which your gamers, your gamers are.

434
00:28:57,217 --> 00:28:59,938
Not some people, your gamers, your gamers are.

435
00:29:00,527 --> 00:29:05,153
And while you should plan ahead, you should also be prepared for changes,

436
00:29:05,153 --> 00:29:08,177
because our market is dynamic as hell.

437
00:29:08,177 --> 00:29:10,320
Everything changes.

438
00:29:10,320 --> 00:29:12,623
And you're going to have to adjust your campaign.

439
00:29:12,623 --> 00:29:15,146
You're going to have to adjust your strategy.

440
00:29:16,139 --> 00:29:23,265
This balance between keeping things as they should be and adjusting them on the go,

441
00:29:23,265 --> 00:29:29,150
this is the perfect thing that you should grasp. And I am happy to tell you that I think that

442
00:29:29,150 --> 00:29:37,117
we have grasped it and it worked for us a lot. And last but not least, good marketing is important,

443
00:29:37,117 --> 00:29:43,682
but good game is a must. Because good marketing can build you kind of a foundation for the launch,

444
00:29:43,682 --> 00:29:45,343
can build the hype.

445
00:29:45,624 --> 00:29:49,389
but you have maintained the hype with your game

446
00:29:49,389 --> 00:29:53,595
and maintained the hype with all the things that you do

447
00:29:53,595 --> 00:29:56,058
around your game in the long run.

448
00:29:56,058 --> 00:29:59,543
So yeah, so that is all from my side.

449
00:29:59,543 --> 00:30:00,965
Thank you very much for your time.

450
00:30:00,965 --> 00:30:01,906
It was a pleasure for me.

